## Description {#details}

<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/x86ii">X86II</a> - This namespace holds all of the target specific flags that instruction info tracks.

### anonymous enum  {#a74027296f130de8cbbe7bc543dc4285e}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>anonymous enum : uint64&#95;t</>}>

<EnumerationList title="Enumeration values">

<Link id="a74027296f130de8cbbe7bc543dc4285eac147ba1bbcbb4cbda038e4fbd6e5bb31" />
<EnumerationListItem name="Pseudo">
PseudoFrm - This represents an instruction that is a pseudo instruction or one that has not been implemented yet (= 0)
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a74027296f130de8cbbe7bc543dc4285ea0418cac03c72116432f2161ba81a9477" />
<EnumerationListItem name="RawFrm">
Raw - This form is for instructions that don&#39;t have any operands, so they are just a fixed opcode value, like &#39;leave&#39; (= 1)
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a74027296f130de8cbbe7bc543dc4285ea5cd1bb6ca4bb8d7b507c98b61a19ae77" />
<EnumerationListItem name="AddRegFrm">
AddRegFrm - This form is used for instructions like &#39;push r32&#39; that have their one register operand added to their opcode (= 2)
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a74027296f130de8cbbe7bc543dc4285eaf45ee1f86f45fd23ef8e084b0069aa17" />
<EnumerationListItem name="RawFrmMemOffs">
RawFrmMemOffs - This form is for instructions that store an absolute memory offset as an immediate with a possible segment override (= 3)
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a74027296f130de8cbbe7bc543dc4285eab93edaca89956bd35deb0830c0a83c32" />
<EnumerationListItem name="RawFrmSrc">
RawFrmSrc - This form is for instructions that use the source index register SI/ESI/RSI with a possible segment override (= 4)
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a74027296f130de8cbbe7bc543dc4285ea336cd3807e9712aee813c92ab1cbd3c7" />
<EnumerationListItem name="RawFrmDst">
RawFrmDst - This form is for instructions that use the destination index register DI/EDI/RDI (= 5)
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a74027296f130de8cbbe7bc543dc4285ea0ebbf8b9bdbf40355e1786a06fe3ebdb" />
<EnumerationListItem name="RawFrmDstSrc">
RawFrmDstSrc - This form is for instructions that use the source index register SI/ESI/RSI with a possible segment override, and also the destination index register DI/EDI/RDI (= 6)
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a74027296f130de8cbbe7bc543dc4285ea682f4bde7ea50ebb5d09cfc9f8283d87" />
<EnumerationListItem name="RawFrmImm8">
RawFrmImm8 - This is used for the ENTER instruction, which has two immediates, the first of which is a 16-bit immediate (specified by the imm encoding) and the second is a 8-bit fixed value (= 7)
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a74027296f130de8cbbe7bc543dc4285eab246efb880b0f5ea54ddf3879bced8e3" />
<EnumerationListItem name="RawFrmImm16">
RawFrmImm16 - This is used for CALL FAR instructions, which have two immediates, the first of which is a 16 or 32-bit immediate (specified by the imm encoding) and the second is a 16-bit fixed value (= 8)
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a74027296f130de8cbbe7bc543dc4285ea3db5b7855daab5b642f29a4f8743d1a9" />
<EnumerationListItem name="AddCCFrm">
AddCCFrm - This form is used for Jcc that encode the condition code in the lower 4 bits of the opcode (= 9)
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a74027296f130de8cbbe7bc543dc4285ea3f6747b02d6858c6b951b760c4117325" />
<EnumerationListItem name="PrefixByte">
PrefixByte - This form is used for instructions that represent a prefix byte like data16 or rep (= 10)
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a74027296f130de8cbbe7bc543dc4285ea7ea417afb58cc07fa2cfcae87905361c" />
<EnumerationListItem name="MRMDestRegCC">
MRMDestRegCC - This form is used for the cfcmov instructions, which use the Mod/RM byte to specify the operands reg(r/m) and reg(reg) and also encodes a condition code (= 18)
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a74027296f130de8cbbe7bc543dc4285eaa9e2dd541cca69dae4eb2b19c12a920a" />
<EnumerationListItem name="MRMDestMemCC">
MRMDestMemCC - This form is used for the cfcmov instructions, which use the Mod/RM byte to specify the operands mem(r/m) and reg(reg) and also encodes a condition code (= 19)
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a74027296f130de8cbbe7bc543dc4285ea39ff7e3b87758fceb290c859e5525b92" />
<EnumerationListItem name="MRMDestMem4VOp3CC">
MRMDestMem4VOp3CC - This form is used for instructions that use the Mod/RM byte to specify a destination which in this case is memory and operand 3 with VEX.VVVV, and also encodes a condition code (= 20)
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a74027296f130de8cbbe7bc543dc4285ea47511fb3305bca93e2f5a8b5c06cd434" />
<EnumerationListItem name="MRMr0">
Instructions operate on a register Reg/Opcode operand not the r/m field (= 21)
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a74027296f130de8cbbe7bc543dc4285ea912fe30bf2fb6db485900f399a0f6919" />
<EnumerationListItem name="MRMSrcMemFSIB">
MRMSrcMem - But force to use the SIB field (= 22)
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a74027296f130de8cbbe7bc543dc4285ea5a693dd88d31ce75ba797dca591201dc" />
<EnumerationListItem name="MRMDestMemFSIB">

</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a74027296f130de8cbbe7bc543dc4285ea8de627e0b4d8f49621aaffaf22768ccf" />
<EnumerationListItem name="MRMDestMem">
MRMDestMem - This form is used for instructions that use the Mod/RM byte to specify a destination, which in this case is memory (= 24)
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a74027296f130de8cbbe7bc543dc4285eabeb3b7e6c5b8fde8b53c453b462f0aae" />
<EnumerationListItem name="MRMSrcMem">
MRMSrcMem - This form is used for instructions that use the Mod/RM byte to specify a source, which in this case is memory (= 25)
</EnumerationListItem>

<EnumerationListItem name="MRMSrcMem4VOp3">
MRMSrcMem4VOp3 - This form is used for instructions that encode operand 3 with VEX.VVVV and load from memory (= 26)
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a74027296f130de8cbbe7bc543dc4285eabfcb56e85f0547829052a6f31803159b" />
<EnumerationListItem name="MRMSrcMemOp4">
MRMSrcMemOp4 - This form is used for instructions that use the Mod/RM byte to specify the fourth source, which in this case is memory (= 27)
</EnumerationListItem>

<EnumerationListItem name="MRMSrcMemCC">

  labels = {["inline"]}>
Compute whether all of the def operands are repeated in the uses and therefore should be skipped.

This determines the start of the unique operand list. We need to determine if all of the defs have a corresponding tied operand in the uses. Unfortunately, the tied operand information is encoded in the uses not the defs so we have to use some heuristics to find which operands to query.
